Former Aviation Minister, Femi Fani-Kayode, has reacted to reports of the First Lady, Aisha Buhari abandoning the Presidential Villa, Abuja for Dubai. Mrs Buhari was reported to have abandoned the Nigerian Presidential Villa for Dubai over security concerns The First Lady has not returned to the country since September after the wedding of her daughter, Hanan. While Mrs Buhari is in Dubai, President Muhammadu Buhari is currently in his hometown of Daura, Katsina State. Reacting, Fani-Kayode described the current situation as a bad omen. The former Minister also lamented over reports of the Chief Justice of the Federation, CJN, Mohammed Tanko and Army generals contracting COVID-19. In a tweet, the former minister wrote: “The President is in his home town of Daura having “a rest”. “The First Lady is in Dubai due to security challenges in the Presidential Villa, the Chief Justice has COVID-19, the Chief of Army Staff is in isolation, a number of Army Generals have COVID-19. These are bad omens.”